The paper discusses the diffusion of information in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information sciences. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also uses Twitter data, which involves analyzing large amounts of text, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of a model, which could fall under cs.DL (Machine Learning) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper discusses the influence of external sources on information diffusion, which could fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
